# 🛡️ AWS AI-Powered Threat Detection Pipeline

A real-time, event-driven cloud security system that automatically detects and responds to threats in an AWS environment using fully managed, serverless services.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates a production-style security pipeline that monitors AWS activity, detects threats using machine learning, and delivers instant, human-readable alerts — all without managing a single server.

The scenario simulates a compromised EC2 instance making outbound connections to a known malicious (blackhole) IP address — a real-world threat pattern classified by AWS as `Trojan:EC2/BlackholeTraffic`.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
CloudTrail (API Logs)
        │
        ▼
  Amazon GuardDuty  ──── ML + Threat Intel ────▶ Threat Finding
        │
        ▼
  Amazon EventBridge  (Event Pattern Filter)
        │
        ▼
  AWS Lambda  (Alert Formatter)
        │
        ▼
  Amazon SNS  ──────────────────────────────────▶ Email Alert
```

---

## ☁️ AWS Services Used

| Service | Role |
|---|---|
| **Amazon GuardDuty** | AI/ML-powered continuous threat detection |
| **AWS CloudTrail** | Captures all API calls and account activity |
| **Amazon EventBridge** | Routes specific GuardDuty findings to downstream targets |
| **AWS Lambda** | Parses raw GuardDuty JSON and formats a readable alert |
| **Amazon SNS** | Delivers the formatted email notification to the security team |
| **AWS IAM** | Enforces least-privilege permissions across services |

---

## 🔍 Why This Architecture

**GuardDuty** removes the need to build or maintain threat rules. It uses Amazon's own ML models and continuously updated threat intelligence feeds to detect anomalies across CloudTrail logs, VPC Flow Logs, and DNS queries — covering a wide attack surface automatically.

**EventBridge** acts as a zero-latency event router. Instead of polling for findings, it pushes events the moment GuardDuty raises an alert, enabling true real-time response.

**Lambda** bridges the gap between raw machine-generated findings and human-readable notifications. GuardDuty findings are dense JSON payloads — Lambda extracts the signal (instance ID, remote IP, finding type, region, timestamp) and turns it into a clear, actionable message.

**SNS** delivers the alert to any subscriber — email, SMS, or downstream SIEM — making it trivially easy to notify the right people without building notification infrastructure.

**CloudTrail** is the foundational data source. Without it, GuardDuty has no API-level visibility. Enabling it ensures every action in the account is logged and available for analysis.

